ges.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=815%2C543 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1223%2C815 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1631%2C1087 4x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=407%2C271, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=815%2C543 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1223%2C815 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1631%2C1087 4x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=555%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1110%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1667%2C1111 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=2222%2C1481 4x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=555%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1110%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1667%2C1111 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=2222%2C1481 4x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"ERG mode explained: what is it, how to use it and when you should turn it off\" title=\"ERG mode explained: what is it, how to use it and when you should turn it off\" src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/02/20191018_SB_5DSR_MG_8246-b6b675a.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\"></picture></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> ERG mode is one of the key features of smart trainers, which can communicate wirelessly to computer programs and apps.</span></figcaption><p><span><i>Simon Bromley / Immediate Media</i></span></p></div><p>ERG mode is a setting in training platforms such as <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/features/zwift-your-complete-guide/\">Zwift</a>, <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/reviews/training/training-software/trainerroad-training-software-review/\">TrainerRoad</a> and <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/reviews/training/training-software/the-sufferfest-training-centre-app-review/\">Sufferfest</a> that fixes your power output by automatically adjusting your resistance to match your cadence.</p><p>Power is a calculation of torque (how hard you’re pressing on the pedals) multiplied by cadence (how fast they are turning). ERG mode uses the two in tandem to ensure you hit the prescribed power output.</p><p>As an example, if a workout requires you to hold 200 watts, the resistance will automatically increase if your cadence drops, or decrease if your cadence increases, in order to keep you at 200 watts.</p><p>This is in contrast with other trainer modes, where the onus is on you to adjust your resistance and cadence in order to hit your target power.</p><p>Perhaps not surprisingly, ERG mode only works with pre-built workouts because it requires a target power to be defined, otherwise the trainer wouldn’t know how much resistance to apply.</p><p>However, the latest <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/best-indoor-cycling-apps/\">indoor cycling apps</a> offer a wide range of <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/fitness-and-training/best-workouts-training-plans-zwift/\">workouts and training plans</a>, and also allow you to build your own.</p><h2>Benefits of ERG mode</h2><div><picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/Indoor-training-on-Zwift-4c9764c.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=299%2C199, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/Indoor-training-on-Zwift-4c9764c.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=599%2C399 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/Indoor-training-on-Zwift-4c9764c.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=899%2C599 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/Indoor-training-on-Zwift-4c9764c.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1199%2C799 4x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/Indoor-training-on-Zwift-4c9764c.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=299%2C199, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/Indoor-training-on-Zwift-4c9764c.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=599%2C399 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/Indoor-training-on-Zwift-4c9764c.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=899%2C599 3x, https://im